---
layout: layouts/base.njk
pageTitle: "Funeral Homes, Cemeteries & Death Care Services in Schuylkill County"
description: "Find trusted funeral homes, cemeteries, cremation services, and monument companies in Schuylkill County, PA. A free community directory for Coal Region families."
---

<div class="container">
  <h1>Death Care Services in Schuylkill County, PA</h1>
  <p class="page-intro">
    Finding the right provider during a difficult time shouldn't be hard. This directory lists every locally-owned funeral home, cemetery, cremation service, and monument company serving families in the Coal Region.
  </p>

  <div class="card-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);">
    {% for cat in businesses.categories %}
      <a href="/{{ cat.slug }}/" class="category-card">
        <span class="count">{{ cat.items.length }}</span>
        <span class="label">{{ cat.label }}</span>
      </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Browse by City</h2>
    <div class="city-links">
      {% for city in businesses.cities %}
        {% if city.items.length >= 2 %}
          <a href="/cities/{{ city.slug }}/">{{ city.name }} ({{ city.items.length }})</a>
        {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Planning Ahead?</h2>
    <p class="page-intro">
      Most Schuylkill County funeral homes offer pre-planning services. Making arrangements in advance lifts a tremendous burden from your loved ones during an already difficult time.
    </p>
    <div class="city-links">
      <a href="/guides/pre-planning-funeral-checklist/">Pre-Planning Checklist</a>
      <a href="/guides/what-to-do-when-someone-dies-in-pa/">What to Do When Someone Dies in PA</a>
      <a href="/guides/veterans-burial-benefits-pa/">Veterans Burial Benefits</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "name": "{{ site.title }}",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}",
  "description": "{{ site.description }}"
}
</script>
